title: i-Recommend Wholeheartedly
text:
Features a two layer design; the inner layer is silicone and the outer layer is a hard plastic with an embedded plastic fold-out stand. The fold-out stand is great for hands free movie watching.
The case itself protects well from bumps and bruises. I have dropped by phone onto a bare tile floor at work several times and it looks no worse for the wear. Excllent protection.
It has elevated edges around the screen. This helps to protect the screen from direct contact when face down. Unfortunately, these raised edges make it a little difficult to pull down the notification drawer when in landscape mode. Not a huge deal; just push some of the flexible silicone out of the way before you swipe down. I'd rather have the protection than have a bare screen, though.
The case also comes with a belt holster with a nice fabric spot facing your screen. The clip on the holster also turns into a stand. It seemed a bit odd at first because this only allows you to face the back towards you. After a few moments, I realized that this allowed me to aim the rear speaker directly at me while placing the phone on a desk or counter.
Protection and added features in the same package. Defintely consider this case if you own an S4 Active.

title: A combination product that gets it right!
text:
Just got this product and it definitely doesn't dissappoint. The ink pen worked from the moment it hit paper and has kept on writing. The stylus is awesome, too. Instead of those squishy rubber tips that don't glide across the screen very well, this nib is made out of some kind of conductive "micro-knit" material. It's still got some give like the rubber nibs, but it slides across the screen as smoothly as if it were made out of silk. It's worked without a hitch on every device I've tried it on from my phone to my tablet; even the touch screen monitor at work.

Build quality and size are good too. Not too heavy and not too light either. I believe that the entire body is made out of metal, so it should hold up to some significant abuse.

Overall, it's 100% recommended.

text: This is the best screen and device protection skin on the market. I have bought for my last four iDevices. It is relatively easy to install, follow the readily available youtube tutorials, they are great guides. Suggestion to help the protector dry, and seal and help relieve some air bubbles use a hair drier alternating between the cool and slightly warm settings (don't use extreme heat, could be bad for device and skin), if in doubt use cool setting. title: Hearty case for $12.99, Lifeproof esque feel.
text:
Hefty case for the price. While it does not offer all the same protection as life proof (waterproof ) but it compares in slimness and usability.
Pros:
1. Fingerprint sensor is functional (I contacted them about a defect in the original product in the fingerprint sensor cover I had and they sent me a new case that appears to be defect free. They were easy to work with.)
2. Slim, similar to Lifeproof. Good for if you drop your phone.
3. The metal plate on back gives it some weight and balance.
4. Volume and power buttons function as they are supposed to function.

Cons:
1. Port covers, seem to be weak points especially at the hinges.
2. Extremely difficult to open once phone is in
3. Vibrate/silence switch cover, same weakness as the port covers.

This case is good quality for the price of $12.99 (since this post was originally the price has risen to $17.99; still a descent value at that price at about a quarter of the price of Lifeproof). It provides great protection for the iPhone 6.

Tips: 1. Don't forget to remove the plastic on the inside front panel. It hides in there and will cause you issues such as touch screen malfunction and fingerprint sensor malfunction.
2. If you have issues contact them they are very capable of helping you and they are friendly.

Overall I will give this four stars because I don't feel that my experience with the accessories included in this is typical and because the screen protector itself still works very well.

title: Very high end feel, over the moon for this case!
text:
[[VIDEOID:a5f0e0a361cb3aab7c01e41a587b25b]] I purchased this case after being let down with another one I got from a different brand that was fantastic except for their “anti yellow” promise that fell through within only a couple months. I've seen this case pop up a few times in my searching and finally decided to just go for it based on the positive reviews. I saw one guy go very in depth about what he likes in a case and how he spends a lot of time looking- honestly mood, finally someone gets it. I definitely agree with almost everything he says about this case except for one thing which is the tactile (or ‘click-y as I say) feel of the buttons. For my case, the home button is pretty responsive and doesn't take a lot of pressure to push. However, the volume buttons definitely take effort which honestly isn't THAT devastating since I typically pull down on the screen if I wanna adjust my volume for whatever I'm listening to. So meh, didn't take away a star for that because I figure that's just me nitpicking.

Moving on! I chose pink which is extremely out of character for me but I'm so happy I did. I was worried it'd be a silly shade that didn't suit me, but it's a beautiful soft pastel pink that feels more neutral than anything.

The materials this case is made of feels very high end and I'm here for it. When I say it feels durable, I mean it. It's not flimsy or floppy, it has shape to it and a certain hardness that feels assuring. Quick shoutout to the precise cutouts and the raised camera lip!

Onto my favorite part- the thin and minimalist features which are to swoon over. There is no annoying branding, the case isn't chunky by any means, and it's just so simple that you'll be constantly staring and wondering how this product doesn't have more sales. Like seriously, I'm so minimalist when it comes to my phone that I don't have a single icon/app showing unless you look at the bottom main row. This case completes that vibe of a clean, breathable feel and it's appreciated.

The bumpers, another nice feature, seem like they'll actually do some protecting. I'm elated they don't protrude which I was afraid of- they actually sit nearly flush (aligned) with the rest of the case. Lastly, the free stand is not only -super- functional, but it feels surprisingly high quality considering it's a freebie. I don't think I'm gonna use it a lot but I'm always gonna have it with me in case someone is in need of one. But man, it's the little stuff like that which brings the whole thing full circle to being a wonderful purchase.

Overall, I'm so freaking excited and happy with this case. I wish I could get free ones like some people have (nudge nudge to the company) but regardless I'm happy to buy more in different colors assuming this current one holds up and keeps me satisfied. My next color will either be the light green or alpine green, but I hope one day to own all colors. I'm really rooting for more to come out too, such as possibly maroon, lilac, a milk tea color (very soft shade of light brown), yellow, maybe some neons, etc.

Anyways, I'm in love with what I got. My boyfriend is even constantly reminding me of how nice it is! He is due for a new case and judging by how much he looks at mine, it's safe to say a purchase from him is coming soon as well. Thank you to this company for making a gorgeous product. I obsess over finding the perfect case which usually leads to frustration and a head ache, but buying this spontaneously has been one of my favorite decisions I've made in a hot minute. By the way, I LOVE how you can still see the Apple logo through the back. Another thing to note- this case does have grip to it.

Hope this helps someone who tends to get obsessive as well, I know how horrifyingly tedious it can be to search for a hundred hours just to not find anything or be let down. Give this case a try if you're looking for similar qualities. (:

title: Easiest application, dirties easily…
text:
This is my first time using a Spigen screen protector as I normally go with the other brands that have good reviews. However, seeing as how other Spigen screen protectors had extremely positive and glowing reviews, I thought I would spend a little more and give them a fair try.

The box came with two applicators with the screen protectors built in, wet cleaning wipes, a dry cleaning cloth, lint stickers, instructions, a squeegee, and a small misc card. Installation itself was a tiny bit confusing at first since this was my first time using this style, but after a rereading or two I was like “oh okay” and it was smooth sailing from there (my personal instructions are in the last paragraph).

Transparent thoughts- I love how easy and precise the application is, but wow does it get dirty fast. Other screen protectors I've bought (I'm talking half the price for a 3 pack) have both been bubble free installation and stayed very clean for a while before losing the oleophobic coating. This one I've had for less than 24 hours and it's a lint magnet, has prints all over it, and cleans very smudgy which is terrible. I will make both of these last as long as I can, but I won't be buying them again. I'm super picky, so if you don't care about the little stuff and just want your phone protected, this is the way to go. Anyways, all in all they're not perfect but not the worst I've ever tried. I give them an honest 4/5.

In case anyone is confused or needs more in depth instructions: wipe the phone with a wet wipe, wipe with the dry cloth, use a big lint sticker all over, make sure the applicator has the side with the pull tab face down (the side with the sticker with the numbers 1-3 should be face up), peel and quickly place the applicator down onto the phone, press in the middle and slide from 1 to 3, wait 30 seconds, peel from 3 to 1, lift up applicator, peel the tab off the screen protector, then squeegee out bubbles and you're done. TIP: if you're a perfectionist like me who despises even a single lint under the protector, before applying the applicator to the phone hold the screen protector in the right hand while blowing and getting ready to peel, then give one last good blow and very quickly peel and apply. This will ensure you get a flawless application without having to lift up the glass to try and sticker off any lint.

Thank you for reading, I hope this helps someone out. I've attached photos including one of the back so people know this is a real review from a real paying customer with a real iPhone 13 Pro Max lol.

title: A nearly flawless case!
text:
Update after 3 months of having this case:
Still 5 stars! I actually just upgraded to a new case, but I wanted to say this case never once scratched or marked up my phone in any way, caused any problems, or faded in color/quality. Actually, I had an accidental drop from my lap onto concrete recently while rushing out of a car and my phone didn't have a single crack or scratch show up as the case took the full blow. I must say, I'm officially impressed with this case.

So I had ordered a $30 case from a well-known brand that said matte and when it came, it was clear and overall a terrible product, aside from having exposed buttons. I was hesitant to try again, let alone this product because of it not having many reviews, but I am beyond happy I did!

This case is SUPER thin, lightweight, nice to look at, sleek, and it is what it says it is- frosted! I love these kind because they truly don't get any smudges or scuffs like the clear cases do, yet it's clear just enough so the whole phone can be seen! So this product is definitely 100% accurate in the description, especially with these precise cutouts- I'm very impressed!

My ooooooonly complaint is that the buttons (volume and power) are kinda sunken into the cutouts, so it requires a little more effort to push. I originally thought the buttons would stick out to make for easier pressing. However, it's not a big deal at all which is why I'm not gonna deduct a star. Maybe the makers of this can come up with an updated version or a second version where they give those area-like cutouts instead of the precise ones.

I'm not sure how this will fare when dropped, and I don't plan on dropping it because I'm very careful with iPhones, but to be completely honest this case is so thin that I strongly doubt it would give any kind of protection. This is one of those cases where you need to either have a pop socket, get insurance, be diligent while using on the move, or all of the above. If you're clumsy, I'd advise against this one.

Overall I'm extremely happy with how this looks! They makers really know how to apply precision and aesthetic into their products, and to think it's half of what I paid for the low-quality case from the other company? MNML, you have a returning and loyal customer now. Thank you!

Side note: Definitely use with a screen protector as this case will not protect the front!

Overall, highly pleased. Quite a nice case for a very reasonable price.

text:
I tried approximately 50 cases from Samsung, Supcase, iBlason, Latercase, Ghostek, Ringke, Caka, Cresee, Speck, Hummix, Torras, Ruky, Spigen, VRS, Vihibii, Shieldon, Sheid, Fewdew, and others and sent them all back.

My search is finally over for the best case for this phone! Buy with absolute confidence!!!!

This model has a slide out tray that holds your phone which is good if you dont have a remote to control the phone when in the headset, as it makes it easy to slide out quickly tap next video and slide it back in with little hassle.

The only reason this headset has not received a 5 star rating is because other models had a removable front to keep phone cool and this only has a few little vents. I did find my phone gettin slightly warmer in this design.

All in all this headset feels well made and works as designed. I would recommend it for purchase as it is just as good as other units that were $20+ more. If you have any questions you can email me difectly and i will try to help you out the best i can.

title: Very cool 3-in-1 wireless car charger
text:
[[VIDEOID:551d675ccc3b0a2070780265bac3169]] This is a pretty cool car charger. It allows multiple wireless charging devices to be charged with a single charger. It makes it a little bigger in size than some other chargers. However, the functionality makes up for it.

Pluses
1. Charge a Qi or Qi compatible phone, along with an iWatch (with included charging pad) and Airpods (slot in top-back of charger)
2. Simple button opens the charger, then closes around the phone automatically. Use same button to open the charger to remove phone.
3. Comes with a dashboard mounting kit as well as vent mount
4. The package includes a quick charge DC adapter

Minuses
1. Bulky, large
2. Galaxy Buds case too thick to fit into Airpod charging slot

I was unable to actually test the watch & headphone charging options. But I can report that the wireless charging function works great with a Samsung Galaxy Note 20 Ultra 5G & Galaxy S20FE.

title: Very good car charger but missing a crucial part
text:
[[VIDEOID:e982d54ec2c15714696060592413c9a6]] This is a very good car charger. It's small in size, allowing it to fit onto a vent and not block too much of the dash. However, this kit is missing a very crucial part to its operation.

Pluses
1. Charge a Qi or Qi compatible phone
2. Charger automatically sets the correct placement of the phone for optimum charging
3. Comes with a vent mount and USB charging cable

Minuses
1. No DC power adapter included in box

Once the charger is mounted to a vent & plugged into power adapter, press the button (raised dots) on top of the charging unit. The charger will open up. Place the phone onto the charger. It will automatically orient itself to find the optimum position for the phone. Press the top button again and it'll open itself up to allow removal of the phone. I can report that the wireless charging function works great with a Samsung Galaxy Note 20 Ultra 5G & Galaxy S20FE.

However, not including the DC power adapter is a major issue, in my opinion. Most USB ports in vehicles don't supply enough power for the quick charging function. And what if you don't have a USB port in your vehicle or an extra DC power adapter? Kind of inconvenient.

If you already have a DC power adapter, then no concerns. This is a good charger.

title: Great quality UV phone cleaner

Minuses

title: Solidly constructed, super fast charging
text:
This is a high quality, excellent build quality, fast charging car charger.

The charger comes packed into a zippered carrying case. Included is a single USB-C to USB-C charging cable & a user manual.

The charger is solid metal construction, unlike a lot of other chargers that are mostly plastic. It snapped into the car charging port with a solid thunk. Vents around the base of the unit allow for heat dissipation.

When plugged into the top 68w charging port, a Samsung Galaxy Note 20 Ultra registers super fast charging mode. This allowed my phone to get a 50% charge within 25 minutes. Better than some other fast chargers that I've used in the past.

title: Galaxy S10 is a solid Android phone
text:
Got this slighlty used phone for my wife as a replacement for a Samsung Galaxy S8.

The screen size is not overly large, which works with her sensibilities of not wanting to carry around a mega screen phone.

The fingerprint reader, screen brightness and choices to customize the phone to her liking is what my wife likes about the phone. The 128GB internal storage works perfect for app installs & the like.

However, the big bonus is the inclusion of a microSD card slot. This allows a person to add a ton of more storage at a lower price point that buying the phone with more internal storage. Internal storage may be faster, but in the value-vs-reward trade-off, I'd rather have the extra space at lower cost. My wife agrees, as the 256GB microSD card I installed satisfies all of her storage requirements.

The Samsung Galaxy S21 is now selling, so this review may not be as relevant anymore. However, anyone looking for a good Android phone without the high price should give the Galaxy S10 a serious look.

title: Excellent quality glass screen protector
text:
Excellent quality glass screen protector. Upscale, high quality retail packaging. Perfect fit for Samsung GS5. Fits about 99% of the screen. Kit contains all of technology items needed for successful install.

Once screen is cleaned & dried, use dust removal tape to remove any lingering dust particles. Remove the adhesive from glass protector, turn over & apply to phone screen. Be careful not to touch side that goes on phone screen. Once set, press the protector down. It will literally seal itself to phone screen. Then just go over it with dry cloth to remove any bubbles (should be very few). If you should see dust particle, lift the protector from the edge, use dust tape to remove dust, then try again. Pretty easy install, much easier than plastic film.
